Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content: yes.

Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content: What it does is pull listunspnt, filter iguana utxos out and saves then, then every time iguana asks it simply gives is one and removes it from the list, all in ram, bypasses wallet.

Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content: so you could hvabe a staking wallet running and it would just ignore it... in fact the more utxo you have the better it would work, because it doesnt have to "reload" as often.

Content: Need to make sure its safe though, maybe if you consolidated utxos, it would be passing iguana spent ones.
